    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.37a.6"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">6</fw>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    What porridge had John Keats? 
                        <lb/>
                    --Browning
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 23, 1973</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Poet,</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>I am compiling a cookbook, to be published by Doubleday, which will feature favorite recipes of contemporary American poets.</p>
                
                <p>The recipes may be original with the poet, may be the poet's variation on a standard recipe, or may be simply a favorite standard recipe.</p>
                
                <p>Would you send me a copy of your favorite recipe? I need to have the recipes by May 20, 1973. Please indicate below which category describes your recipe.</p>
                
                <p>Also, you may choose to add, for publication, a few brief comments concerning the recipe, but this is not absolutely necessary.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Victoria McCabe</signed>
                    <signed>Victoria McCabe</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>331 Broadway</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Pueblo, Colorado <add>81004</add></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <note>
                    <hi rend="caps">R.P.</hi> Dickey, 
                    husband,
                    Says you'll have a good one <unclear>or</unclear> two! 
                </note>
                
                Variation of the firehole cooking method an outdoor cooking. 
                <del/>
                dig a <del>w</del><add>h</add>ole 2 feet square and 2 feet deep &#8212; 
                2x2x2&#8212; 
                kindle a fire in the hole and keep putting an larger chunks of firewood to generate a good bed of coals &#8212;
                Inclose a <add>stuffed</add> fowl &#8212; goose, duck or chicken sew up in <del><unclear/>oase</del><add>coarse</add> muslin sack &#8212;
                peel needed potatoes
                <unclear reason="missing"/>
                
            </div1>
